### Proof

We are given that `F ≤ G` and we want to prove that `map f F ≤ map f G`. By definition of the order on filters, this means that every set in `map f G` is also in `map f F`. 

Take any set `S` in `map f G`. By the definition of `map`, there exists a set `T ∈ G` such that `S = f '' T`. Since `F ≤ G`, we have `T ∈ F`. Therefore, `S = f '' T` is also in `map f F`, as required.

### Lean 4 Proof

